Overview:

The Smart Waste Management System aims to revolutionize waste collection and disposal in smart cities using IoT technology. This project integrates sensors, microcontrollers, and a mobile application to optimize waste management processes and promote environmental sustainability.

Key Features:
Real-time monitoring of waste levels using ultrasonic sensors.
Automatic lid operation with servo motors upon detecting nearby persons.
Detection of water levels using moisture sensors coupled with DC motors.
Gas and flame sensors for detecting harmful substances in bins.
GPS tracking for real-time location monitoring.
Live streaming capability through integrated camera modules.

Technologies Used:
Hardware: ESP32 microcontroller, Arduino software, IoT sensors.
Software: Arduino IDE was utilized for coding and development.
Mobile App Development: MIT App Inventor used for creating the mobile application interface.